THE WEST ZONE message board | SHOP NOW: DEALS on CLEMSON apparel
Clemson's coaches take pride in their penchant for playing a substantial portion of their first-year freshmen, having used nearly half of last year’s signing class en route to the national championship.
The Tigers will finish National Signing Day today with a considerably smaller class than their standard, which figures to proportionally cut the number of freshmen who play next season, too.
